LinearCongruentialGenerator - Class in com.andreamazzon.session3.lazyinitialization
This class generates pseudo random numbers through a linear congruential random number generator: as you will see, a linear congruential random number generator produces natural numbers x[i+1] =(a*x[i] +c) mod_m, where x[0] = seed, for appropriate values of natural numbers a, c and m (for big m).
